# TypeScript with Payload

**Docs:** [TypeScript](https://payloadcms.com/docs/typescript/overview)

## Generated types

- **`pnpm generate:types`** after collection/global/field/plugin changes (`typescript.outputFile` → usually `payload-types.ts`).
- **Relations:** prefer generated unions (`number | Media`) + runtime narrowing over `as any`.
- **Cloud types:** separate files when CMS vs Cloud APIs differ.
- **Do not** hand-roll large interfaces that **generate:types** can produce unless bridging externals.

## Naming — hand-written code

- **Suffix `ID`**, not `Id`, for identifiers you own (`docID`, `teamID`, `mediaID`). Align with Payload fields like **`customID`**. **Acronyms:** **`DB`** not `Db` (`payloadDB.ts`, `resolvePayloadDB`).
- **Generated props:** use names from `payload-types.ts` as-is; bridge with `const xID = doc.xId` only until schema rename + regenerate.
- **Exceptions:** React **`useId`**, DOM **`getElementById`**, wire-format keys from remote APIs — unchanged.

**Globals helpers:** `src/lib/resolveGlobalField.ts`, `src/globals/globalSlugs.ts`.

## Checklist

- [ ] **generate:types** when schema changes (or document manual step).
- [ ] Use **`Config`** collection slug unions where appropriate (`getDocument`).

